Verification Phase: bridge between work done and money paid\
\
The protocol replaces a centralized manager with a decentralized "court of experts."\
\
The Bounty Verification Logic has 2 components: (A) the "Expert Court", followed by (B) the Curation Logic (ie "Wisdom of Crowds").\
\
A)  The Bounty Verification Flow ("The Expert Court")\
Used for releasing funds ($500 - $100k) after a researcher claims to be finished.\
\
The Visual Scene:\
\
The Submission: A researcher uploads their code/PDF. This is sealed with a digital fingerprint (IPFS Hash) so it can't be changed later.\
The Summoning: The Smart Contract randomly selects 3-5 Platinum Tier curators (Authority Score > 2,000). They get a notification/ping: "New Verification Task Pending."\
\
\
Bounty Verification Mermaid:\
\
sequenceDiagram\
    participant R as Researcher\
    participant C as Smart Contract\
    participant V as Verifier Pool (Platinum)\
    participant W as Researcher Wallet\
\
    rect rgb(20, 20, 30)\
        Note over R, C: Phase 1: Submission\
        R->>C: Submit Work (IPFS Hash)\
        C->>C: Lock State: "Under Review"\
    end\
\
    rect rgb(30, 30, 40)\
        Note over C, V: Phase 2: The Summoning\
        C->>V: Randomly select 3 Verifiers\
        V-->>R: (Notification sent)\
    end\
\
    rect rgb(40, 40, 50)\
        Note over V, C: Phase 3: The Verdict (72h Window)\
        V->>V: Review Proof of Work\
        V->>C: Vote: \uc0\u9989  Approve or \u10060  Reject\
    end\
\
    rect rgb(20, 50, 20)\
        Note over C, W: Phase 4: Execution\
        alt Majority = Approve\
            C->>W: \uc0\u55357 \u56496  Release $10,000 Bounty\
