B. The Curation Verification Flow ("The Wisdom of Crowds")\
Used for verifying the quality of a paper (Breakthrough vs. Noise).\
\
The Visual Scene:\
\
Staking: 10 different researchers enter a room. To speak, they must put $50 on the table (Stake).\
Secret Ballot: They each write their rating of a paper on a card (Breakthrough, Valuable, or Noise). They drop it in a box. They cannot copy each other.\
The Reveal: After the timer ends, the box opens.\
The Convergence:\
If 7 say "Valuable" and 3 say "Noise", the Truth is "Valuable."\
The 7 who agreed get their $50 back + profit.\
The 3 who were wrong lose a portion of their $50.\
Note: High Authority curators have "louder voices" (weighted voting).\
\
visualizing the result: Imagine a heat map on the paper. If the map is tight and red-hot around "Valuable", verification is successful and confidence is high. If the map is scattered all over, verification failed (low confidence).}